73/* Legacy X.509 library.
74 *
75 * This header is part of OpenSSL's X.509 implementation. It is retained for
76 * compatibility but otherwise underdocumented and not actively maintained. In
77 * the future, a replacement library will be available. Meanwhile, minimize
78 * dependencies on this header where possible. */

81/*******************************/
82/*
83SSL_CTX -> X509_STORE
84 -> X509_LOOKUP
85 ->X509_LOOKUP_METHOD
86 -> X509_LOOKUP
87 ->X509_LOOKUP_METHOD
88
89SSL -> X509_STORE_CTX
90 ->X509_STORE
91
92The X509_STORE holds the tables etc for verification stuff.
93A X509_STORE_CTX is used while validating a single certificate.
94The X509_STORE has X509_LOOKUPs for looking up certs.
95The X509_STORE then calls a function to actually verify the
96certificate chain.
97*/
98
99#define X509_LU_X509 1
100#define X509_LU_CRL 2
101#define X509_LU_PKEY 3
102
103typedef struct x509_object_st
104 {
105 /* one of the above types */
106 int type;
107 union {
108 char *ptr;
109 X509 *x509;
110 X509_CRL *crl;
111 EVP_PKEY *pkey;
112 } data;
113 } X509_OBJECT;
114
115DEFINE_STACK_OF(X509_LOOKUP)
116DEFINE_STACK_OF(X509_OBJECT)
117
118/* This is a static that defines the function interface */
119typedef struct x509_lookup_method_st
120 {
121 const char *name;
122 int (*new_item)(X509_LOOKUP *ctx);
123 void (*free)(X509_LOOKUP *ctx);
124 int (*init)(X509_LOOKUP *ctx);
125 int (*shutdown)(X509_LOOKUP *ctx);
126 int (*ctrl)(X509_LOOKUP *ctx,int cmd,const char *argc,long argl,
127 char **ret);
128 int (*get_by_subject)(X509_LOOKUP *ctx,int type,X509_NAME *name,
129 X509_OBJECT *ret);
130 int (*get_by_issuer_serial)(X509_LOOKUP *ctx,int type,X509_NAME *name,
131 ASN1_INTEGER *serial,X509_OBJECT *ret);
132 int (*get_by_fingerprint)(X509_LOOKUP *ctx,int type,
133 unsigned char *bytes,int len,
134 X509_OBJECT *ret);
135 int (*get_by_alias)(X509_LOOKUP *ctx,int type,char *str,int len,
136 X509_OBJECT *ret);
137 } X509_LOOKUP_METHOD;
138
139typedef struct X509_VERIFY_PARAM_ID_st X509_VERIFY_PARAM_ID;
140
141/* This structure hold all parameters associated with a verify operation
142 * by including an X509_VERIFY_PARAM structure in related structures the
143 * parameters used can be customized
144 */
145
146struct X509_VERIFY_PARAM_st
147 {
148 char *name;
149 time_t check_time; /* Time to use */
150 unsigned long inh_flags; /* Inheritance flags */
151 unsigned long flags; /* Various verify flags */
152 int purpose; /* purpose to check untrusted certificates */
153 int trust; /* trust setting to check */
154 int depth; /* Verify depth */
155 STACK_OF(ASN1_OBJECT) *policies; /* Permissible policies */
156 X509_VERIFY_PARAM_ID *id; /* opaque ID data */
157 };
158
159DEFINE_STACK_OF(X509_VERIFY_PARAM)

161typedef int (*X509_STORE_CTX_verify_cb)(int, X509_STORE_CTX *);
162typedef int (*X509_STORE_CTX_verify_fn)(X509_STORE_CTX *);
163typedef int (*X509_STORE_CTX_get_issuer_fn)(X509 **issuer,
164 X509_STORE_CTX *ctx, X509 *x);
165typedef int (*X509_STORE_CTX_check_issued_fn)(X509_STORE_CTX *ctx,
166 X509 *x, X509 *issuer);
167typedef int (*X509_STORE_CTX_check_revocation_fn)(X509_STORE_CTX *ctx);
168typedef int (*X509_STORE_CTX_get_crl_fn)(X509_STORE_CTX *ctx,
169 X509_CRL **crl, X509 *x);
170typedef int (*X509_STORE_CTX_check_crl_fn)(X509_STORE_CTX *ctx, X509_CRL *crl);
171typedef int (*X509_STORE_CTX_cert_crl_fn)(X509_STORE_CTX *ctx,
172 X509_CRL *crl, X509 *x);
173typedef int (*X509_STORE_CTX_check_policy_fn)(X509_STORE_CTX *ctx);
174typedef STACK_OF(X509) *(*X509_STORE_CTX_lookup_certs_fn)(X509_STORE_CTX *ctx,
175 X509_NAME *nm);
176typedef STACK_OF(X509_CRL) *(*X509_STORE_CTX_lookup_crls_fn)(X509_STORE_CTX *ctx,
177 X509_NAME *nm);

180/* This is used to hold everything. It is used for all certificate
181 * validation. Once we have a certificate chain, the 'verify'
182 * function is then called to actually check the cert chain. */
183struct x509_store_st
184 {
185 /* The following is a cache of trusted certs */
186 int cache; /* if true, stash any hits */
187 STACK_OF(X509_OBJECT) *objs; /* Cache of all objects */
188 CRYPTO_MUTEX objs_lock;
189 STACK_OF(X509) *additional_untrusted;
190
191 /* These are external lookup methods */
192 STACK_OF(X509_LOOKUP) *get_cert_methods;
193
194 X509_VERIFY_PARAM *param;
195
196 /* Callbacks for various operations */
197 X509_STORE_CTX_verify_fn verify; /* called to verify a certificate */
198 X509_STORE_CTX_verify_cb verify_cb; /* error callback */
199 X509_STORE_CTX_get_issuer_fn get_issuer; /* get issuers cert from ctx */
200 X509_STORE_CTX_check_issued_fn check_issued; /* check issued */
201 X509_STORE_CTX_check_revocation_fn check_revocation; /* Check revocation status of chain */
202 X509_STORE_CTX_get_crl_fn get_crl; /* retrieve CRL */
203 X509_STORE_CTX_check_crl_fn check_crl; /* Check CRL validity */
204 X509_STORE_CTX_cert_crl_fn cert_crl; /* Check certificate against CRL */
205 X509_STORE_CTX_lookup_certs_fn lookup_certs;
206 X509_STORE_CTX_lookup_crls_fn lookup_crls;
207 X509_STORE_CTX_cleanup_fn cleanup;
208
209 CRYPTO_refcount_t references;
210 } /* X509_STORE */;
211
212OPENSSL_EXPORT int X509_STORE_set_depth(X509_STORE *store, int depth);
213
214/* This is the functions plus an instance of the local variables. */
215struct x509_lookup_st
216 {
217 int init; /* have we been started */
218 int skip; /* don't use us. */
219 X509_LOOKUP_METHOD *method; /* the functions */
220 char *method_data; /* method data */
221
222 X509_STORE *store_ctx; /* who owns us */
223 } /* X509_LOOKUP */;
224
225/* This is a used when verifying cert chains. Since the
226 * gathering of the cert chain can take some time (and have to be
227 * 'retried', this needs to be kept and passed around. */
228struct x509_store_ctx_st /* X509_STORE_CTX */
229 {
230 X509_STORE *ctx;
231
232 /* The following are set by the caller */
233 X509 *cert; /* The cert to check */
234 STACK_OF(X509) *untrusted; /* chain of X509s - untrusted - passed in */
235 STACK_OF(X509_CRL) *crls; /* set of CRLs passed in */
236
237 X509_VERIFY_PARAM *param;
238 void *other_ctx; /* Other info for use with get_issuer() */
239
240 /* Callbacks for various operations */
241 X509_STORE_CTX_verify_fn verify; /* called to verify a certificate */
242 X509_STORE_CTX_verify_cb verify_cb; /* error callback */
243 X509_STORE_CTX_get_issuer_fn get_issuer; /* get issuers cert from ctx */
244 X509_STORE_CTX_check_issued_fn check_issued; /* check issued */
245 X509_STORE_CTX_check_revocation_fn check_revocation; /* Check revocation status of chain */
246 X509_STORE_CTX_get_crl_fn get_crl; /* retrieve CRL */
247 X509_STORE_CTX_check_crl_fn check_crl; /* Check CRL validity */
248 X509_STORE_CTX_cert_crl_fn cert_crl; /* Check certificate against CRL */
249 X509_STORE_CTX_check_policy_fn check_policy;
250 X509_STORE_CTX_lookup_certs_fn lookup_certs;
251 X509_STORE_CTX_lookup_crls_fn lookup_crls;
252 X509_STORE_CTX_cleanup_fn cleanup;
253
254 /* The following is built up */
255 int valid; /* if 0, rebuild chain */
256 int last_untrusted; /* index of last untrusted cert */
257 STACK_OF(X509) *chain; /* chain of X509s - built up and trusted */
258 X509_POLICY_TREE *tree; /* Valid policy tree */
259
260 int explicit_policy; /* Require explicit policy value */
261
262 /* When something goes wrong, this is why */
263 int error_depth;
264 int error;
265 X509 *current_cert;
266 X509 *current_issuer; /* cert currently being tested as valid issuer */
267 X509_CRL *current_crl; /* current CRL */
268
269 int current_crl_score; /* score of current CRL */
270 unsigned int current_reasons; /* Reason mask */
271
272 X509_STORE_CTX *parent; /* For CRL path validation: parent context */
273
274 CRYPTO_EX_DATA ex_data;
275 } /* X509_STORE_CTX */;
276

375/* Certificate verify flags */
376
377/* Send issuer+subject checks to verify_cb */
378#define X509_V_FLAG_CB_ISSUER_CHECK 0x1
379/* Use check time instead of current time */
380#define X509_V_FLAG_USE_CHECK_TIME 0x2
381/* Lookup CRLs */
382#define X509_V_FLAG_CRL_CHECK 0x4
383/* Lookup CRLs for whole chain */
384#define X509_V_FLAG_CRL_CHECK_ALL 0x8
385/* Ignore unhandled critical extensions */
386#define X509_V_FLAG_IGNORE_CRITICAL 0x10
387/* Does nothing as its functionality has been enabled by default. */
388#define X509_V_FLAG_X509_STRICT 0x00
389/* Enable proxy certificate validation */
390#define X509_V_FLAG_ALLOW_PROXY_CERTS 0x40
391/* Enable policy checking */
392#define X509_V_FLAG_POLICY_CHECK 0x80
393/* Policy variable require-explicit-policy */
394#define X509_V_FLAG_EXPLICIT_POLICY 0x100
395/* Policy variable inhibit-any-policy */
396#define X509_V_FLAG_INHIBIT_ANY 0x200
397/* Policy variable inhibit-policy-mapping */
398#define X509_V_FLAG_INHIBIT_MAP 0x400
399/* Notify callback that policy is OK */
400#define X509_V_FLAG_NOTIFY_POLICY 0x800
401/* Extended CRL features such as indirect CRLs, alternate CRL signing keys */
402#define X509_V_FLAG_EXTENDED_CRL_SUPPORT 0x1000
403/* Delta CRL support */
404#define X509_V_FLAG_USE_DELTAS 0x2000
405/* Check selfsigned CA signature */
406#define X509_V_FLAG_CHECK_SS_SIGNATURE 0x4000
407/* Use trusted store first */
408#define X509_V_FLAG_TRUSTED_FIRST 0x8000
409/* Suite B 128 bit only mode: not normally used */
410#define X509_V_FLAG_SUITEB_128_LOS_ONLY 0x10000
411/* Suite B 192 bit only mode */
412#define X509_V_FLAG_SUITEB_192_LOS 0x20000
413/* Suite B 128 bit mode allowing 192 bit algorithms */
414#define X509_V_FLAG_SUITEB_128_LOS 0x30000
415
416/* Allow partial chains if at least one certificate is in trusted store */
417#define X509_V_FLAG_PARTIAL_CHAIN 0x80000
418
419/* If the initial chain is not trusted, do not attempt to build an alternative
420 * chain. Alternate chain checking was introduced in 1.0.2b. Setting this flag
421 * will force the behaviour to match that of previous versions. */
422#define X509_V_FLAG_NO_ALT_CHAINS 0x100000
423
424#define X509_VP_FLAG_DEFAULT 0x1
425#define X509_VP_FLAG_OVERWRITE 0x2
426#define X509_VP_FLAG_RESET_FLAGS 0x4
427#define X509_VP_FLAG_LOCKED 0x8
428#define X509_VP_FLAG_ONCE 0x10
429
430/* Internal use: mask of policy related options */
431#define X509_V_FLAG_POLICY_MASK (X509_V_FLAG_POLICY_CHECK \
432 | X509_V_FLAG_EXPLICIT_POLICY \
433 | X509_V_FLAG_INHIBIT_ANY \
434 | X509_V_FLAG_INHIBIT_MAP)
